1
00:00:18,460 --> 00:00:20,821
Exterminate!

2
00:00:20,823 --> 00:00:23,118
Aaagh!

3
00:00:23,120 --> 00:00:25,958
The Doctor must be destroyed!

4
00:00:25,960 --> 00:00:30,358
Earth is protected by me and my
mates, this year and every other.

5
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:31,838
Here we go!

6
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:33,440
Exterminate!

7
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:37,438
- Now attach the parts.
- Weapon failure.

8
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:39,218
- The parts are on, Doctor!
- Get clear!

9
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,398
Is everyone all right in there?

10
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:11,638
We had an accident.

11
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:13,358
People got hurt.

12
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:14,678
The issue's been dealt with.

13
00:01:15,722 --> 00:01:19,341
There'll be someone
waiting at Depository 23.

14
00:01:19,343 --> 00:01:21,463
Long time since we opened that one.

15
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:26,240
Whatever that is, is it safe?

16
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:29,960
Just get it there quick as you can.

17
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:32,898
Am I allowed to stop for a cuppa?

18
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:35,078
Oh, only 'cause it's you.

19
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:36,358
How's your mum, by the way?

20
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:39,758
- Yeah, you know...
- Must be hard.

21
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:42,760
Yeah. Best get on the road.

22
00:02:10,513 --> 00:02:12,712
- Hi.
- Hi.

23
00:02:12,714 --> 00:02:15,514
Can I get a cup of tea in
there, please? Thank you.

24
00:02:19,453 --> 00:02:21,692
- There you go, love.
- Cheers.

25
00:02:21,694 --> 00:02:23,894
- Have a good day.
- Thanks very much. Have a good one.

26
00:04:11,799 --> 00:04:13,678
When you said breakfast meeting,

27
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:16,278
I presumed it would be somewhere
that served breakfast.

28
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:18,706
- Jo Patterson.
- Leo Rugazzi.

29
00:04:18,708 --> 00:04:20,478
CEO, Rugazzi Technologies.

30
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:22,658
I acquired Leo's company 18 months ago.

31
00:04:22,660 --> 00:04:25,398
I see you buying a lot
of companies right now.

32
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,738
They're calling you the
American Mike Ashley.

33
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:32,490
There's a lot of value
in the market today.

34
00:04:32,492 --> 00:04:34,570
Having your political ambitions ruined

35
00:04:34,572 --> 00:04:36,370
by that little toxic waste scandal

36
00:04:36,372 --> 00:04:38,811
seems to have been
a blessing in disguise.

37
00:04:38,813 --> 00:04:41,490
That's a very sensitive subject for me.

38
00:04:41,492 --> 00:04:44,050
I just wanted to say
that I am super-psyched

39
00:04:44,052 --> 00:04:47,930
about having a proper
Technology Secretary at last.

40
00:04:47,932 --> 00:04:49,439
I was super-psyched too,

41
00:04:49,441 --> 00:04:52,330
until they told me that
my budget was £2.70.

42
00:04:52,332 --> 00:04:55,130
Well, if anybody can make
it work, it's you, Jo.

43
00:04:55,132 --> 00:04:56,930
Show me why we're here.

44
00:04:56,932 --> 00:04:58,530
Leo has something...

45
00:04:58,532 --> 00:05:00,812
...revolutionary to show you.

46
00:05:07,972 --> 00:05:09,732
Just a small role-play.

47
00:05:10,572 --> 00:05:13,770
We all know the problems
facing the world today.

48
00:05:13,772 --> 00:05:17,370
Trust in our leaders
is at an all-time low.

49
00:05:17,372 --> 00:05:20,690
Civil unrest is growing.

50
00:05:20,692 --> 00:05:23,730
Security budgets are falling.

51
00:05:23,732 --> 00:05:26,932
Our police forces are under pressure.

52
00:05:31,772 --> 00:05:33,770
Goodness, I hope no-one's
going to get hurt.

53
00:05:33,772 --> 00:05:36,892
The problem is obvious.
Here's the solution.

54
00:06:04,022 --> 00:06:06,142
Built-in water cannon.

55
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:13,850
And CS gas.

56
00:06:13,852 --> 00:06:16,690
We're not using actual CS gas.

57
00:06:16,692 --> 00:06:18,972
I still think it would have been fine.

58
00:06:29,172 --> 00:06:31,332
Sonic deterrent!

59
00:06:35,932 --> 00:06:39,550
Entirely robotic with an
AI interface programme

60
00:06:39,552 --> 00:06:41,650
for every eventuality,

61
00:06:41,652 --> 00:06:45,210
thanks to extensive
real-world scenario testing.

62
00:06:45,212 --> 00:06:48,970
Er, solar... solar powered
with A-grade energy rating.

63
00:06:48,972 --> 00:06:50,570
You built this yourself?

64
00:06:50,572 --> 00:06:54,010
Oh, pretty much. Um, once
Mr. Robertson became involved,

65
00:06:54,012 --> 00:06:56,270
he really helped us
turbo-boost the whole project.

66
00:06:56,272 --> 00:06:58,030
Actually, talking about...

67
00:06:58,032 --> 00:07:00,918
Er, she gets the picture,
Leo. That's fine.

68
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,360
This is a game-changer, Jo.

69
00:07:04,932 --> 00:07:07,432
It's the security equivalent
of the iPhone.

70
00:07:13,052 --> 00:07:14,652
Shall we talk in private?

71
00:07:17,511 --> 00:07:20,910
I want them built and beta
tested in my constituency.

72
00:07:20,912 --> 00:07:22,410
Yes, yes, as discussed.

73
00:07:22,412 --> 00:07:26,010
When those car firms deserted
you, I bought up all the plants.

74
00:07:26,012 --> 00:07:32,729
I own them now. So we repurpose
new infrastructure, new jobs.

75
00:07:32,731 --> 00:07:35,090
This is going to be
a big win for you, Jo.

76
00:07:35,092 --> 00:07:40,690
A flagship policy from our dynamic
new Technology Secretary

77
00:07:40,692 --> 00:07:45,292
and it looks like, er, your party's
going to need a new leader soon.

78
00:07:46,612 --> 00:07:49,090
What does he know, young Leo?

79
00:07:49,092 --> 00:07:52,010
Only that I got the parts
from some unknown source.

80
00:07:52,012 --> 00:07:54,210
If it ever gets out
that I tipped you off

81
00:07:54,212 --> 00:07:57,790
about advanced technology
being transported from GCHQ...

82
00:07:57,792 --> 00:07:59,490
It won't.

83
00:07:59,492 --> 00:08:01,570
We trust each other.

84
00:08:01,572 --> 00:08:03,490
This is a good arrangement, Jo.

85
00:08:03,492 --> 00:08:06,370
You're simply facilitating
an acquisition

86
00:08:06,372 --> 00:08:09,010
and I'm cutting you in on the IP.

87
00:08:09,012 --> 00:08:10,330
Nobody knows.

88
00:08:10,332 --> 00:08:12,330
Everybody wins.

89
00:08:12,332 --> 00:08:13,572
How long will it take?

90
00:08:14,732 --> 00:08:18,652
Er, a year, give or take.

91
00:08:59,932 --> 00:09:02,490
Ugh...

92
00:09:08,223 --> 00:09:09,783
Morning, camera 37.

93
00:09:12,972 --> 00:09:15,132
Morning, camera 38.

94
00:09:42,652 --> 00:09:44,172
Morning, Angela.

95
00:09:54,252 --> 00:09:55,852
All right, Bonnie and Clyde?

96
00:10:02,172 --> 00:10:03,370
Tiny!

97
00:10:03,372 --> 00:10:05,450
How many times?

98
00:10:05,452 --> 00:10:08,930
You can't eat the cage.
Believe me, I've tried.

99
00:10:27,903 --> 00:10:29,463
Bedtime story, Doctor?

100
00:10:30,252 --> 00:10:31,890
Yes, please, Doctor.

101
00:10:31,892 --> 00:10:33,511
One of the classics?

102
00:10:33,513 --> 00:10:35,513
Ooh, yes, please.

103
00:10:37,212 --> 00:10:38,892
Settle down, then.

104
00:10:41,859 --> 00:10:45,918
"Mr. and Mrs. Dursley, of number
four Privet Drive, were proud to say

105
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:48,399
that they were perfectly normal..."

106
00:10:49,292 --> 00:10:50,412
What?

107
00:10:58,732 --> 00:11:00,852
Who's there?

108
00:11:10,532 --> 00:11:11,772
Stay strong.

109
00:11:13,612 --> 00:11:15,452
People are waiting for you.

110
00:11:47,079 --> 00:11:50,278
I keep thinking she was barely
in here for a couple of minutes

111
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:52,410
and yet she coded the
entry lock to our DNA,

112
00:11:52,412 --> 00:11:54,092
just like on her own TARDIS.

113
00:11:55,532 --> 00:11:58,923
Maybe that's 'cause she wanted
us to be able to follow her,

114
00:11:58,925 --> 00:12:00,330
to find her,

115
00:12:00,332 --> 00:12:02,810
'cause she needed us.

116
00:12:02,812 --> 00:12:04,212
I'm going to work it out.

117
00:12:05,212 --> 00:12:06,890
I must be able to work it out.

118
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:09,132
Happy New Year, Yaz.

119
00:12:11,932 --> 00:12:13,850
When was it New Year?

120
00:12:13,852 --> 00:12:15,810
You been sleeping in here?

121
00:12:15,812 --> 00:12:17,092
Maybe.

122
00:12:21,012 --> 00:12:24,410
Yaz, you can't keep
being here all the time.

123
00:12:24,412 --> 00:12:27,370
The Doc, you know, she went to do
something she knew might kill her.

124
00:12:27,372 --> 00:12:29,572
- We've just got to assume she didn't make it.
- Why?

125
00:12:31,132 --> 00:12:32,930
Why do we have to assume that?

126
00:12:32,932 --> 00:12:34,492
Mate, we've been back ten months.

127
00:12:35,492 --> 00:12:37,088
We have to get on with our lives.

128
00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:39,569
That's what she told us.
That's what she wanted for us.

129
00:12:39,571 --> 00:12:41,570
But what if she needs us?

130
00:12:41,572 --> 00:12:42,930
How many times has she saved us?

131
00:12:42,932 --> 00:12:44,930
Yaz, face up to it, we
don't know how to find her.

132
00:12:44,932 --> 00:12:46,490
All right?

133
00:12:46,492 --> 00:12:47,972
And there's something else.

134
00:12:49,052 --> 00:12:51,132
- Graham, show her.
- Mm-hm.

135
00:12:52,972 --> 00:12:56,010
The Doc would really want us to
keep an eye on the planet, right?

136
00:12:56,012 --> 00:12:59,210
Look, this is leaked online footage

137
00:12:59,212 --> 00:13:02,410
of what they're calling a
prototype security drone.

138
00:13:02,412 --> 00:13:05,672
Apparently, this was taken
over a year ago. Just watch.

139
00:13:08,532 --> 00:13:10,692
- That's a Dalek.
- Mm-hm.

140
00:13:13,012 --> 00:13:15,090
But how's that possible?

141
00:13:15,092 --> 00:13:17,372
- No idea.
- Watch.

142
00:13:20,092 --> 00:13:21,690
Jack Robertson.

143
00:13:21,692 --> 00:13:23,610
- Spider guy.
- Mm.

144
00:13:23,612 --> 00:13:25,290
He's in league with a Dalek?

145
00:13:25,292 --> 00:13:27,490
That's what we're going to find out.

146
00:13:27,492 --> 00:13:30,290
And that's what the Doc would
do if she was here, so...

147
00:13:30,292 --> 00:13:32,232
...are you with us?

148
00:13:37,096 --> 00:13:39,735
Well, it's an honour

149
00:13:39,737 --> 00:13:42,317
to be summoned by the
Prime Minister in waiting...

150
00:13:43,212 --> 00:13:46,490
...even if it is a bit, er, rural.

151
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:48,930
How many hours till we get
the results from the ballots?

152
00:13:48,932 --> 00:13:50,890
The numbers are on my side.

153
00:13:50,892 --> 00:13:52,430
That's why I wanted to talk.

154
00:13:52,432 --> 00:13:54,610
You're not having doubts
about our agreement, are you?

155
00:13:54,612 --> 00:13:56,490
Quite the opposite.

156
00:13:56,492 --> 00:13:58,730
I want to expedite our project.

157
00:13:58,732 --> 00:14:01,770
Six of the sweetest words
in the English language.

158
00:14:01,772 --> 00:14:05,330
I want an immediate national
roll-out of security drones.

159
00:14:05,332 --> 00:14:06,850
National?

160
00:14:06,852 --> 00:14:10,250
But we've only just started
regional beta testing.

161
00:14:10,252 --> 00:14:12,850
And I want it at no cost
to the British taxpayer.

162
00:14:14,292 --> 00:14:18,270
Why, Jo, this is starting
to sound like a shakedown.

163
00:14:18,272 --> 00:14:22,037
This country can be your
shop window for global sales.

164
00:14:22,039 --> 00:14:25,398
Unless, of course, you'd like
the Treasury to take a look

165
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:28,920
at how much tax all your
companies pay over here?

166
00:14:30,596 --> 00:14:34,356
Ah. Well played...

167
00:14:35,789 --> 00:14:37,389
...Prime Minister.

168
00:14:38,630 --> 00:14:39,990
Well played.

169
00:14:41,389 --> 00:14:44,047
Leo? I'm outside.

170
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:45,427
Three minutes.

171
00:14:45,429 --> 00:14:47,309
Yo. Remember us?

172
00:14:48,469 --> 00:14:51,747
Take the car! Just leave my face.

173
00:14:51,749 --> 00:14:53,029
What?

174
00:14:54,869 --> 00:14:59,147
Oh, no! Not you guys!

175
00:14:59,149 --> 00:15:02,947
Yeah, us, 'cause we know
all about you and that Dalek.

176
00:15:02,949 --> 00:15:05,307
- The what?
- The Dalek.

177
00:15:05,309 --> 00:15:07,947
The most deadly creature in the
universe. We saw you with it.

178
00:15:07,949 --> 00:15:10,198
What is this word that you keep using?

179
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:12,598
Oh, don't play innocent! Dalek.

180
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:14,707
Whatever you're doing with
it, we're going to stop you.

181
00:15:14,709 --> 00:15:17,427
Hands in the air!
Step away from the car!

182
00:15:17,429 --> 00:15:19,528
What, you didn't think
I'd increase my security

183
00:15:19,530 --> 00:15:21,170
since the last time we met?

184
00:15:22,189 --> 00:15:25,347
You're lucky you're not
all dead on the ground.

185
00:15:25,349 --> 00:15:27,889
Get rid of 'em, boys.

186
00:15:30,879 --> 00:15:33,678
Well, that didn't go
exactly to plan, did it?

187
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,598
I like that whole
"whatever you're doing,

188
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,528
we're going to stop you"
vibe. Very Doctory.

189
00:15:37,530 --> 00:15:38,787
Doesn't work when I do it.

190
00:15:38,789 --> 00:15:41,147
We didn't get anywhere near
an explanation from him.

191
00:15:41,149 --> 00:15:43,239
If we had the Doctor's psychic paper

192
00:15:43,241 --> 00:15:44,857
or we knew how to work that TARDIS,

193
00:15:44,859 --> 00:15:47,139
we could get into his office
and see what's going on.

194
00:15:48,709 --> 00:15:50,247
Yeah, but we don't, so we're going

195
00:15:50,249 --> 00:15:51,907
to have to try and
figure out another way.

196
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:53,349
Yeah. This is hard, innit?

197
00:16:06,949 --> 00:16:08,589
Morning, camera 38.

198
00:16:22,149 --> 00:16:25,347
Oh, I forgot you were here.

199
00:16:25,349 --> 00:16:27,149
What about this face?

200
00:16:28,669 --> 00:16:30,269
Remember this?

201
00:16:32,669 --> 00:16:34,389
Jack?

202
00:16:35,469 --> 00:16:36,547
Jack!

203
00:16:36,549 --> 00:16:39,187
I knew you would look better
in these colours than me.

204
00:16:39,189 --> 00:16:40,907
Hello, Doctor.

205
00:16:40,909 --> 00:16:42,307
What are you doing here?

206
00:16:42,309 --> 00:16:44,427
What do you think I'm doing
here? Breaking you out.

207
00:16:44,429 --> 00:16:48,187
Temporal-freezing gateway
disinhibitor bubble. Catchy, right?

208
00:16:48,189 --> 00:16:51,267
If it were me, I'd have
called it a breakout ball.

209
00:16:51,269 --> 00:16:54,107
Freezes time temporarily,
breaks through walls.

210
00:16:54,109 --> 00:16:55,707
Only problem is...

211
00:16:55,709 --> 00:16:57,629
...it doesn't last long.

212
00:17:01,909 --> 00:17:03,987
- Hi!
- Have you had work done?

213
00:17:03,989 --> 00:17:05,427
You can talk!

214
00:17:05,429 --> 00:17:06,909
Now shut up and run.

215
00:17:09,629 --> 00:17:12,547
I heard a rumour you were in here,
so I committed a few crimes.

216
00:17:12,549 --> 00:17:15,027
Well, maybe a lot of crimes.
Maybe more than I should have.

217
00:17:15,029 --> 00:17:16,387
What sort of crimes?

218
00:17:16,389 --> 00:17:17,507
- Left turn.
- Oh!

219
00:17:17,509 --> 00:17:19,567
You're going to take the
moral high ground with me

220
00:17:19,569 --> 00:17:21,307
when I'm breaking you out of prison?

221
00:17:21,309 --> 00:17:23,267
- Be grateful!
- Front door!

222
00:17:23,269 --> 00:17:26,109
- How long has this thing got left?
- 11 seconds till expiry!

223
00:17:27,949 --> 00:17:28,988
Go!

224
00:17:32,670 --> 00:17:34,027
Phew!

225
00:17:34,029 --> 00:17:36,587
Took 19 years to get
to the cell next to you.

226
00:17:36,589 --> 00:17:39,387
- Hope you had enough to occupy your mind.
- Too much.

227
00:17:39,389 --> 00:17:42,707
Here we go. One secretly
stashed vortex manipulator.

228
00:17:43,949 --> 00:17:47,467
Wondered how long that would
take. We need to go now.

229
00:17:47,469 --> 00:17:49,587
How did you manage to
smuggle that in here?

230
00:17:49,589 --> 00:17:51,349
You really want me to answer that?

231
00:17:52,469 --> 00:17:54,909
Oh, I've missed you... very much.

232
00:17:56,989 --> 00:17:58,429
Let's go.

233
00:18:01,289 --> 00:18:04,107
Operation, logistics and
production have all been called in.

234
00:18:04,109 --> 00:18:07,198
Everyone has been told maximum
capacity, maximum speed,

235
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:09,478
and our beta partners are
working through the night,

236
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:11,759
training staff, under our supervisors

237
00:18:11,761 --> 00:18:15,197
all under NDAs, of... of course.

238
00:18:15,199 --> 00:18:17,398
I mean, we think we might
have enough in place to...

239
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,627
...well, to make the deadline.

240
00:18:19,629 --> 00:18:21,108
Great.

241
00:18:21,110 --> 00:18:24,747
Great job, Leo. This is
going to be good for us.

242
00:18:24,749 --> 00:18:27,187
I-I can't help but feel a little...

243
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:30,149
...well, you know, a little worried
about the speed of this.

244
00:18:34,269 --> 00:18:35,949
Everybody's worried, Leo.

245
00:18:38,109 --> 00:18:42,027
We live in uncertain times.
Do you want to win?

246
00:18:42,029 --> 00:18:44,020
Embrace the uncertainty.

247
00:18:44,022 --> 00:18:46,142
Live in the worry.

248
00:18:46,909 --> 00:18:49,307
O-Okay. Um, so...

249
00:18:49,309 --> 00:18:52,802
So... there's-there's just something

250
00:18:52,804 --> 00:18:55,427
I-I needed to share on this project.

251
00:18:55,429 --> 00:18:57,608
When I first started
working on that casing,

252
00:18:57,610 --> 00:19:00,387
I broke it down into
the tiniest components.

253
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:03,147
I made it my mission to, well, to
understand everything about it.

254
00:19:03,149 --> 00:19:04,667
Yes, and you did a great job.

255
00:19:04,669 --> 00:19:07,027
These machines are going
to change the world.

256
00:19:07,029 --> 00:19:08,827
I'm not talking about the machines.

257
00:19:08,829 --> 00:19:12,397
I'm talking about what was
inside the original artefact.

258
00:19:12,399 --> 00:19:15,558
There's nothing inside, Leo.
It was a burnt-out shell.

259
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:17,347
Well, that's what I'm
trying to tell you.

260
00:19:17,349 --> 00:19:20,187
This granular investigation
I've been doing, I...

261
00:19:20,189 --> 00:19:23,107
...well, I found something more

262
00:19:23,109 --> 00:19:26,306
organic remnants inside the machine,

263
00:19:26,308 --> 00:19:29,667
tiny cellular traces
scattered across the casing.

264
00:19:29,669 --> 00:19:31,587
Where are you going with this, Leo?

265
00:19:31,589 --> 00:19:32,867
Well...

266
00:19:32,869 --> 00:19:34,829
Look, I'll ju... I'll just show you.

267
00:19:40,509 --> 00:19:41,987
Look.

268
00:19:41,989 --> 00:19:43,854
Just here, see?

269
00:19:43,856 --> 00:19:46,256
I-I took the cellular traces and I...

270
00:19:47,309 --> 00:19:48,667
...and I cloned them.

271
00:19:48,669 --> 00:19:50,429
Grew them.

272
00:19:52,022 --> 00:19:53,342
I grew a creature.

273
00:19:55,709 --> 00:19:58,309
Oh, my God!

274
00:19:59,509 --> 00:20:01,987
- It's beautiful, isn't it?
- No!

275
00:20:01,989 --> 00:20:03,787
Are you insane?!

276
00:20:03,789 --> 00:20:06,747
That's the most disgusting
thing I've ever seen in my life.

277
00:20:06,749 --> 00:20:07,907
What were you thinking?

278
00:20:07,909 --> 00:20:09,987
What? It's intelligent.

279
00:20:09,989 --> 00:20:11,889
I hooked it into the
intra-neural network

280
00:20:11,891 --> 00:20:14,007
and... and there were
flickers of activity.

281
00:20:14,009 --> 00:20:15,567
It understood our systems immediately.

282
00:20:15,569 --> 00:20:16,907
You did what?!

283
00:20:16,909 --> 00:20:18,787
All right. Not another word.

284
00:20:18,789 --> 00:20:20,907
You've overreached, Leo.

285
00:20:20,909 --> 00:20:24,030
- I want this incinerated immediately.
- What?!

286
00:20:24,032 --> 00:20:25,347
No argument!

287
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:28,907
- Ow!
- I don't want to see a trace of this.

288
00:20:28,909 --> 00:20:31,387
This never happened, you
never showed it to me,

289
00:20:31,389 --> 00:20:33,787
this thing never existed.
Do you understand?

290
00:20:33,789 --> 00:20:34,889
Okay, okay.

291
00:20:37,669 --> 00:20:39,667
You know what your problem is, Leo?

292
00:20:39,669 --> 00:20:41,507
You're too clever.

293
00:20:41,509 --> 00:20:44,269
This is why people don't like experts.

294
00:21:22,069 --> 00:21:23,709
I'm sorry.

295
00:21:46,909 --> 00:21:47,949
Hi, love.

296
00:21:49,149 --> 00:21:50,389
It... It's me.

297
00:21:52,269 --> 00:21:55,269
I-I have to go on an urgent
business trip tonight.

298
00:21:57,589 --> 00:21:59,269
Give the kids a kiss from me.

299
00:22:00,949 --> 00:22:02,707
Er...

300
00:22:02,709 --> 00:22:04,429
...I'll call you when I can.

301
00:22:06,749 --> 00:22:07,869
Love you.

302
00:22:09,189 --> 00:22:10,549
Bye.

303
00:22:14,709 --> 00:22:15,909
Love you.

304
00:22:16,949 --> 00:22:18,349
Bye.

305
00:22:21,069 --> 00:22:22,227
Stand.

306
00:22:31,709 --> 00:22:34,069
Good puppet.

307
00:22:40,149 --> 00:22:41,549
We're out.

308
00:22:45,949 --> 00:22:47,709
I'm back.

309
00:22:51,549 --> 00:22:53,269
My own TARDIS.

310
00:22:58,269 --> 00:23:01,907
Captain Jack Harkness,
gold star for rescuing.

311
00:23:01,909 --> 00:23:04,398
Told your friends if you
ever need help, I'd be there.

312
00:23:05,710 --> 00:23:07,267
Wow.

313
00:23:07,269 --> 00:23:08,809
Nice upgrade in here.

314
00:23:10,509 --> 00:23:11,867
Which way's my room?

315
00:23:11,869 --> 00:23:14,387
You don't have a room.
You've never had a room.

316
00:23:14,389 --> 00:23:16,989
I had a suite with its
own cocktail lounge.

317
00:23:18,589 --> 00:23:22,147
They gave you my message,
about the lone Cyberman?

318
00:23:22,149 --> 00:23:23,667
You didn't give it the Cyberium?

319
00:23:23,669 --> 00:23:26,947
- It's a long story. I fixed it. Eventually.
- What?

320
00:23:26,949 --> 00:23:29,067
Just about. Sort of.

321
00:23:29,069 --> 00:23:31,187
Why were you in prison
in the first place?

322
00:23:31,189 --> 00:23:33,347
Evading the Judoon. Twice at once.

323
00:23:33,349 --> 00:23:34,719
Then once I was in,

324
00:23:34,721 --> 00:23:37,096
they took 7,000 other
offences into consideration.

325
00:23:37,098 --> 00:23:38,938
They stopped at seven?

326
00:23:40,589 --> 00:23:42,509
I was in prison for being me...

327
00:23:44,069 --> 00:23:46,469
...right at the point when I
wasn't sure what that meant.

328
00:23:47,709 --> 00:23:50,307
Ah, it's been a tough few decades.

329
00:23:50,309 --> 00:23:52,189
You're okay now, yeah?

330
00:23:53,869 --> 00:23:55,309
Oh, I guess we'll find out.

331
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:57,389
Wakey-wakey.

332
00:23:58,469 --> 00:23:59,808
Hey!

333
00:24:01,149 --> 00:24:02,469
Nice nap?

334
00:24:03,669 --> 00:24:05,189
Thanks for waiting.

335
00:24:06,349 --> 00:24:08,387
I had a lot to think about in there.

336
00:24:08,389 --> 00:24:10,827
And three very special
people I've missed.

337
00:24:10,829 --> 00:24:13,227
- One of them was me, right?
- You never change.

338
00:24:13,229 --> 00:24:14,787
Wish I could say the same.

339
00:24:14,789 --> 00:24:16,507
Right.

340
00:24:16,509 --> 00:24:17,989
Find me my fam.

341
00:24:19,149 --> 00:24:20,907
This is what I've got so far.

342
00:24:20,909 --> 00:24:24,079
Remnants of the Dalek we fought at GCHQ

343
00:24:24,081 --> 00:24:25,987
were cleared but then stolen.

344
00:24:25,989 --> 00:24:29,227
The driver is missing, presumed dead.

345
00:24:29,229 --> 00:24:30,707
Now Robertson's got his hands on it.

346
00:24:30,709 --> 00:24:31,907
Well, he can't have,

347
00:24:31,909 --> 00:24:35,126
because you sent that creature
thing that was inside it

348
00:24:35,128 --> 00:24:36,847
into a supernova, so...

349
00:24:36,849 --> 00:24:38,867
Maybe there's more
of them here on Earth.

350
00:24:38,869 --> 00:24:41,347
And one's got Robertson
under their control.

351
00:24:41,349 --> 00:24:43,228
Ryan, shh!

352
00:24:51,789 --> 00:24:53,029
Please.

353
00:24:54,069 --> 00:24:55,533
Please be her.

354
00:25:15,349 --> 00:25:17,747
Hi! I was in space jail.

355
00:25:17,749 --> 00:25:19,107
You what?

356
00:25:19,109 --> 00:25:20,627
Guess who got her out?

357
00:25:20,629 --> 00:25:22,267
You all met Jack, right?

358
00:25:22,269 --> 00:25:23,809
Hey, silver fox!

359
00:25:25,029 --> 00:25:26,069
Hello.

360
00:25:27,189 --> 00:25:28,989
We were worried about you!

361
00:25:30,738 --> 00:25:32,138
What? How long's it been?

362
00:25:33,713 --> 00:25:35,267
A week?

363
00:25:35,269 --> 00:25:36,309
Two weeks?

364
00:25:37,429 --> 00:25:38,829
Ten months.

365
00:25:40,589 --> 00:25:42,427
Er, whoops!

366
00:25:42,429 --> 00:25:45,007
No, it can't be. I set identical
temporal coordinates

367
00:25:45,009 --> 00:25:46,107
to when I sent you back.

368
00:25:46,109 --> 00:25:48,027
Yeah, but your time
machine ain't the best

369
00:25:48,029 --> 00:25:49,429
at running to time, is it, Doc?

370
00:25:55,749 --> 00:25:57,029
I'm sorry.

371
00:25:58,589 --> 00:26:00,989
Yeah, well, it's done now, so...

372
00:26:02,269 --> 00:26:03,349
Yeah.

373
00:26:07,004 --> 00:26:08,787
So...

374
00:26:08,789 --> 00:26:10,307
...what's new on planet Earth?

375
00:26:10,309 --> 00:26:11,388
Dalek.

376
00:26:50,189 --> 00:26:51,547
Forward.

377
00:26:51,549 --> 00:26:54,107
Further. Further.

378
00:26:54,109 --> 00:26:55,669
What is this place?

379
00:26:57,709 --> 00:26:59,109
What have you done?

380
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:08,409
This is my project.

381
00:27:10,109 --> 00:27:15,507
This is what I have built.

382
00:27:15,509 --> 00:27:18,746
So, it looks like a Dalek,
but it can't be a Dalek...

383
00:27:18,748 --> 00:27:20,267
...unless it is a Dalek!

384
00:27:20,269 --> 00:27:22,507
Trust us. We've seen the footage.

385
00:27:22,509 --> 00:27:24,987
If you scan for Dalek DNA
trace across the planet...

386
00:27:24,989 --> 00:27:27,267
- Oh, she's good.
- Yeah, we all are.

387
00:27:27,269 --> 00:27:29,727
So, you've had dealings
with Daleks as well, then?

388
00:27:29,729 --> 00:27:32,558
Yeah, they killed me once.
Long time ago, no big deal.

389
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:35,347
- You look pretty healthy for a corpse.
- I know, right?

390
00:27:35,349 --> 00:27:37,838
I can be killed but I come
back to life pretty quick.

391
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:41,347
Partially her fault, partially a friend
of hers on Earth called Rose.

392
00:27:41,349 --> 00:27:43,827
But she's trapped in a
parallel universe now.

393
00:27:43,829 --> 00:27:45,547
She's what?

394
00:27:45,549 --> 00:27:47,467
Dalek DNA trace, Japan.

395
00:27:47,469 --> 00:27:51,329
Osaka. Well, sort of.
Not an exact match.

396
00:27:52,149 --> 00:27:53,907
Oh, it's corrupted.

397
00:27:53,909 --> 00:27:56,427
I can't quite make sense of it.

398
00:27:56,429 --> 00:27:58,867
I can check it out. Anyone want to come?

399
00:27:58,869 --> 00:28:00,637
I will!

400
00:28:00,639 --> 00:28:03,198
- I want a word with Robertson direct.
- Yeah, me too.

401
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:05,667
Looks like he's recently
opened a facility in Osaka.

402
00:28:05,669 --> 00:28:08,329
We could check it out,
drop you on the way.

403
00:28:12,109 --> 00:28:14,507
Everyone working at maximum capacity.

404
00:28:17,269 --> 00:28:19,949
Er... Let me call you back.

405
00:28:27,829 --> 00:28:31,867
If you're dealing with Daleks,
you are way out of your depth.

406
00:28:31,869 --> 00:28:33,147
What is that thing?

407
00:28:33,149 --> 00:28:35,067
I want to know what
you're doing right now,

408
00:28:35,069 --> 00:28:36,519
and don't try calling security,

409
00:28:36,521 --> 00:28:38,227
'cause I just blocked your phone lines.

410
00:28:38,229 --> 00:28:40,227
What is the matter with you people? Hmm?

411
00:28:40,229 --> 00:28:43,389
Do you want to know what I'm
doing? I'll show you myself.

412
00:28:50,949 --> 00:28:52,949
Welcome to the production line.

413
00:29:06,709 --> 00:29:08,789
You're making Daleks.

414
00:29:13,709 --> 00:29:17,347
We're 3D-printing security drones.

415
00:29:17,349 --> 00:29:21,227
- What about what's inside?
- There's nothing inside.

416
00:29:21,229 --> 00:29:23,429
It's run by artificial intelligence.

417
00:29:24,229 --> 00:29:26,147
- What?
- Watch.

418
00:29:26,149 --> 00:29:27,347
See?

419
00:29:27,349 --> 00:29:28,589
They're machines.

420
00:29:29,629 --> 00:29:31,649
There's the remote signal unit.

421
00:29:33,712 --> 00:29:35,872
- They're empty.
- Mm-hm.

422
00:29:40,709 --> 00:29:42,787
You're messing with things
you don't understand.

423
00:29:42,789 --> 00:29:44,667
The creature these are modelled on

424
00:29:44,669 --> 00:29:47,947
is the most evil killing
machine in the universe.

425
00:29:47,949 --> 00:29:50,117
You're getting much too excited

426
00:29:50,119 --> 00:29:53,107
about a bunch of 3D-printed shapes.

427
00:29:53,109 --> 00:29:55,187
So what are you doing
at your facility in Osaka?

428
00:29:55,189 --> 00:29:57,027
We don't have a facility in Osaka.

429
00:29:57,029 --> 00:29:59,987
- Yeah, you do.
- No, we don't!

430
00:29:59,989 --> 00:30:01,347
I would know.

431
00:30:01,349 --> 00:30:03,627
It says this is an agricultural park.

432
00:30:03,629 --> 00:30:05,147
Guess this is the future.

433
00:30:05,149 --> 00:30:07,547
- Hmm.
- Vertical farms. All inside.

434
00:30:07,549 --> 00:30:10,467
In my time, there are whole
agri-planets that look like this,

435
00:30:10,469 --> 00:30:12,907
shipping food all over galaxies.

436
00:30:12,909 --> 00:30:15,467
- Your time?
- 51st century.

437
00:30:15,469 --> 00:30:16,747
Get lost!

438
00:30:16,749 --> 00:30:18,827
Seriously. Boeshane Peninsula.

439
00:30:18,829 --> 00:30:20,749
Maybe one day I'll take you there.

440
00:30:22,589 --> 00:30:25,347
- Are they all like you there?
- No.

441
00:30:25,349 --> 00:30:26,789
I'm pretty special.

442
00:30:28,669 --> 00:30:30,429
Had a rough time, then?

443
00:30:32,709 --> 00:30:34,827
Without the Doctor?

444
00:30:34,829 --> 00:30:36,187
I don't know what you mean.

445
00:30:37,669 --> 00:30:39,829
I saw the way you shoved her.

446
00:30:42,050 --> 00:30:44,210
You thought she wasn't
coming back, right?

447
00:30:45,749 --> 00:30:47,627
You're guessing a lot from a shove.

448
00:30:47,629 --> 00:30:50,489
I have my own experience
with the Doctor.

449
00:30:59,029 --> 00:31:00,349
I just missed her.

450
00:31:01,984 --> 00:31:04,503
- I never stopped to think...
- Hey.

451
00:31:04,505 --> 00:31:05,959
When I was with the Doctor,

452
00:31:05,961 --> 00:31:08,345
I saw more than I could
have ever dreamed.

453
00:31:09,749 --> 00:31:11,189
And then...

454
00:31:12,829 --> 00:31:14,467
...we lost each other.

455
00:31:14,469 --> 00:31:16,229
I didn't know what happened to him.

456
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:18,640
If he was alive or...

457
00:31:21,509 --> 00:31:23,789
...if I was ever going
to see him again.

458
00:31:27,509 --> 00:31:29,069
Hard way to live.

459
00:31:32,669 --> 00:31:35,549
Being with the Doctor, you don't
get to choose when it stops...

460
00:31:36,829 --> 00:31:38,389
...whether you leave her or...

461
00:31:40,069 --> 00:31:41,547
...she leaves you.

462
00:31:41,549 --> 00:31:42,909
It felt cruel...

463
00:31:44,389 --> 00:31:46,949
...to be shown something
I couldn't have any more.

464
00:31:49,509 --> 00:31:53,187
Felt like, um, I'd
rather not have known.

465
00:31:53,189 --> 00:31:56,409
I'd rather not have met her,
cos having met her and then...

466
00:31:57,362 --> 00:31:59,202
...being without her, that's worse.

467
00:32:00,549 --> 00:32:02,147
How do you deal with that?

468
00:32:02,149 --> 00:32:05,507
How many people in the
universe get to meet the Doctor,

469
00:32:05,509 --> 00:32:07,189
let alone travel with her?

470
00:32:08,669 --> 00:32:10,549
We're the lucky ones, Yaz.

471
00:32:13,035 --> 00:32:15,475
Enjoy the journey while you're on it.

472
00:32:18,669 --> 00:32:20,269
'Cause the joy...

473
00:32:23,389 --> 00:32:24,989
...is worth the pain.

474
00:32:35,909 --> 00:32:37,187
Locked door.

475
00:32:46,789 --> 00:32:48,069
Thanks.

476
00:32:49,749 --> 00:32:51,427
"Thanks"?

477
00:32:51,429 --> 00:32:52,629
That's it?

478
00:32:54,069 --> 00:32:55,707
Are you feeling insecure?

479
00:32:55,709 --> 00:32:57,749
'Cause you seem to need a lot of praise.

480
00:33:00,749 --> 00:33:02,069
Do I?

481
00:33:03,149 --> 00:33:04,669
Through here.

482
00:33:14,709 --> 00:33:16,667
Those things.

483
00:33:16,669 --> 00:33:19,067
They were what was
inside the Dalek we met.

484
00:33:19,069 --> 00:33:20,669
Inside every Dalek.

485
00:33:24,549 --> 00:33:26,307
This is a clone farm.

486
00:33:26,309 --> 00:33:28,509
They're not growing
food here, they're...

487
00:33:31,399 --> 00:33:32,959
...they're growing Daleks.

488
00:33:40,629 --> 00:33:42,264
As your new Prime Minister,

489
00:33:42,266 --> 00:33:47,227
I can see great opportunities
ahead for this country.

490
00:33:47,229 --> 00:33:50,507
We here in Britain, we've
never been afraid of the future,

491
00:33:50,509 --> 00:33:56,269
but I do understand that what we
all crave right now is security.

492
00:33:57,309 --> 00:33:59,827
Security in our politics,

493
00:33:59,829 --> 00:34:01,947
security in our jobs,

494
00:34:01,949 --> 00:34:05,009
security for our families.

495
00:34:06,589 --> 00:34:11,720
I pledge to bring stability and security

496
00:34:11,722 --> 00:34:14,862
to every aspect of our national life.

497
00:34:15,909 --> 00:34:21,987
Together, we can make
this the age of security.

498
00:34:21,989 --> 00:34:24,467
What's happening here?

499
00:34:24,469 --> 00:34:26,220
What are we actually doing?

500
00:34:26,222 --> 00:34:27,956
Going to Osaka, fast!

501
00:34:27,958 --> 00:34:29,108
What about...?

502
00:34:29,110 --> 00:34:31,187
What about this blue box?

503
00:34:31,189 --> 00:34:34,329
What is it? It's a... It's a doorway?

504
00:34:35,309 --> 00:34:36,747
It can't be.

505
00:34:36,749 --> 00:34:38,187
That was my hallway.

506
00:34:38,189 --> 00:34:39,788
I don't understand.

507
00:34:39,790 --> 00:34:41,118
Should we explain it to him?

508
00:34:41,120 --> 00:34:43,147
No, it's more fun watching him struggle.

509
00:34:43,149 --> 00:34:45,707
As hard as it is for you to
understand, this isn't about you.

510
00:34:45,709 --> 00:34:46,907
This is about Daleks.

511
00:34:46,909 --> 00:34:49,627
Please stop using that
word. It has no meaning.

512
00:34:49,629 --> 00:34:51,747
Yes, it does.

513
00:34:51,749 --> 00:34:55,107
To billions of people, Dalek means hate.

514
00:34:55,109 --> 00:34:58,227
Daleks are creatures
of hate and aggression.

515
00:34:58,229 --> 00:35:01,387
Daleks are insidious,
relentless and clever,

516
00:35:01,389 --> 00:35:04,467
and, like hate, they will
spread if they're not stopped.

517
00:35:04,469 --> 00:35:06,867
Never underestimate a Dalek.

518
00:35:06,869 --> 00:35:10,667
Which is why I am unveiling today

519
00:35:10,669 --> 00:35:15,907
a very exciting, new solution
to an age-old problem.

520
00:35:15,909 --> 00:35:19,866
We will harness the
technological revolution

521
00:35:19,868 --> 00:35:22,496
to enhance your safety.

522
00:35:23,589 --> 00:35:27,867
We will alleviate pressure
on police and security staff

523
00:35:27,869 --> 00:35:31,369
and all without draining
the public purse.

524
00:35:43,469 --> 00:35:47,387
Oi! Can you hurry up
and help me with this?

525
00:35:47,389 --> 00:35:49,387
I need to take a sample of the liquid.

526
00:35:49,389 --> 00:35:51,307
I want to know what it's being fed on.

527
00:35:51,309 --> 00:35:53,478
Might give us a clue on how to stop 'em.

528
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:56,347
Huh. We're going to blow 'em up, kid.

529
00:35:56,349 --> 00:35:58,267
That's how we stop 'em.

530
00:36:27,869 --> 00:36:29,069
Jack!

531
00:36:44,429 --> 00:36:45,793
Get it off me!

532
00:36:45,795 --> 00:36:48,715
Stand still! Yaz, don't move!

533
00:36:55,665 --> 00:36:57,064
Nice shot.

534
00:36:57,066 --> 00:37:00,947
As of now, you will see
new defence drones at work

535
00:37:00,949 --> 00:37:02,829
on Britain's streets...

536
00:37:04,149 --> 00:37:07,549
...in our institutions, at our borders...

537
00:37:08,728 --> 00:37:10,427
...and national monuments.

538
00:37:10,429 --> 00:37:14,787
These technological innovations are set

539
00:37:14,789 --> 00:37:18,649
to make Britain more secure.

540
00:37:36,767 --> 00:37:38,287
You do love a beanie.

541
00:37:39,949 --> 00:37:41,069
Me too.

542
00:37:42,669 --> 00:37:45,467
One of the first things I noticed
about you that night we met.

543
00:37:45,469 --> 00:37:48,187
I thought, "Not everyone can
carry off a yellow beanie.

544
00:37:48,189 --> 00:37:49,829
There's a lad to rely on".

545
00:37:54,269 --> 00:37:56,307
Four minutes to Osaka.

546
00:37:56,309 --> 00:37:57,909
Yeah. Okay.

547
00:38:05,629 --> 00:38:06,949
I'm sorry...

548
00:38:08,149 --> 00:38:09,709
...about the ten months.

549
00:38:11,629 --> 00:38:14,129
More sorry than I can ever really say.

550
00:38:20,162 --> 00:38:23,482
This thing, innit? You never
really quite got the hang of it.

551
00:38:25,384 --> 00:38:27,544
I missed you all...

552
00:38:29,229 --> 00:38:30,949
...so much.

553
00:38:33,189 --> 00:38:34,627
Yeah?

554
00:38:34,629 --> 00:38:36,667
We missed you too.

555
00:38:36,669 --> 00:38:38,189
But you've been good?

556
00:38:39,496 --> 00:38:42,736
- Yeah, maybe it's what I needed.
- Oh, yeah. Huh.

557
00:38:43,749 --> 00:38:45,387
Maybe it was.

558
00:38:45,389 --> 00:38:46,987
Hmm. I saw me dad.

559
00:38:46,989 --> 00:38:49,467
Oh, good. Well, was it good?

560
00:38:49,469 --> 00:38:50,787
He's all right?

561
00:38:50,789 --> 00:38:52,747
Yeah, he's back at the oil rigs again.

562
00:38:52,749 --> 00:38:54,469
Due back in a couple of weeks.

563
00:38:55,389 --> 00:38:58,307
But, yeah, we're good.
We're getting there.

564
00:38:58,309 --> 00:39:01,387
Time to reconnect with him,
time to see me mates,

565
00:39:01,389 --> 00:39:03,609
see what's happening on the old planet.

566
00:39:06,029 --> 00:39:07,909
Lots of work to be done here on Earth.

567
00:39:08,909 --> 00:39:10,769
Yeah. Always.

568
00:39:12,669 --> 00:39:15,149
Well, it sounds like
you enjoyed being back.

569
00:39:18,189 --> 00:39:19,829
It's home.

570
00:39:23,109 --> 00:39:24,469
Yeah.

571
00:39:25,589 --> 00:39:27,347
What's happening with your home?

572
00:39:27,349 --> 00:39:29,749
You know, what happened
to you on Gallifrey?

573
00:39:32,153 --> 00:39:33,673
All life there destroyed.

574
00:39:35,469 --> 00:39:38,187
Thanks to the death
particle and Ko Sharmus.

575
00:39:38,189 --> 00:39:40,526
And the Master? What
did he want with you?

576
00:39:40,528 --> 00:39:42,998
- It doesn't even matter now.
- No, no, no.

577
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:45,707
Don't give me that. Right?
I see what you're doing.

578
00:39:45,709 --> 00:39:47,547
You're trying to avoid the subject.

579
00:39:47,549 --> 00:39:49,387
We've known each other long enough now.

580
00:39:49,389 --> 00:39:51,109
I know when something's changed.

581
00:39:52,829 --> 00:39:54,149
Me too.

582
00:40:03,578 --> 00:40:05,418
I'm not who I thought I was, Ryan.

583
00:40:07,149 --> 00:40:10,669
What I always knew to
be the story of my life...

584
00:40:11,789 --> 00:40:13,109
...isn't true.

585
00:40:14,589 --> 00:40:16,507
I wasn't born on Gallifrey.

586
00:40:16,509 --> 00:40:19,587
Where I'm from, all
the lives I've lived,

587
00:40:19,589 --> 00:40:21,799
some of that has been hidden from me,

588
00:40:21,801 --> 00:40:23,427
and I don't even know how much.

589
00:40:23,429 --> 00:40:24,989
Seriously?

590
00:40:26,709 --> 00:40:28,589
And how do you feel about that?

591
00:40:30,069 --> 00:40:31,349
Mostly...

592
00:40:33,389 --> 00:40:34,907
...angry.

593
00:40:34,909 --> 00:40:38,829
While I was locked away,
all I kept thinking was...

594
00:40:41,429 --> 00:40:44,987
"... If I'm not who I thought
I was, then who am I?"

595
00:40:44,989 --> 00:40:46,587
You're the Doctor.

596
00:40:46,589 --> 00:40:48,929
Same as before, same as always.

597
00:40:49,789 --> 00:40:51,587
Right.

598
00:40:51,589 --> 00:40:53,749
Same Doctor, same Ryan.

599
00:40:55,429 --> 00:40:57,187
Nothing's changed.

600
00:40:57,189 --> 00:40:58,947
No. No.

601
00:40:58,949 --> 00:41:00,429
I didn't say that, did I?

602
00:41:04,829 --> 00:41:09,467
Things change all the time, and
they should, cos they have to.

603
00:41:09,469 --> 00:41:12,067
Same with people.

604
00:41:12,069 --> 00:41:14,139
Sometimes we get a bit scared,

605
00:41:14,141 --> 00:41:16,589
'cause new can be a bit scary, right?

606
00:41:19,229 --> 00:41:21,747
New can be very scary.

607
00:41:21,749 --> 00:41:24,827
So, when we're done
with this Dalek problem,

608
00:41:24,829 --> 00:41:26,749
you find out about your own life.

609
00:41:28,589 --> 00:41:30,749
Confront the new, or the old.

610
00:41:32,269 --> 00:41:35,109
And then everything will be all right.

611
00:41:36,629 --> 00:41:39,027
- Will it?
- No doubt.

612
00:41:43,469 --> 00:41:45,027
What?

613
00:41:45,029 --> 00:41:46,549
Thank you, Ryan...

614
00:41:48,429 --> 00:41:49,989
...for being my friend.

615
00:41:52,109 --> 00:41:53,669
Thank you for being mine.

616
00:41:54,709 --> 00:41:55,949
Always.

617
00:42:01,429 --> 00:42:03,107
Osaka.

618
00:42:07,229 --> 00:42:11,469
Oh-ho-ho! I've missed that sound.

619
00:42:18,029 --> 00:42:19,229
Whoa!

620
00:42:20,469 --> 00:42:22,347
Wait, what just happened?

621
00:42:22,349 --> 00:42:24,387
- Still not telling him?
- No.

622
00:42:24,389 --> 00:42:25,947
Where am I?

623
00:42:25,949 --> 00:42:28,438
- Did you really have to bring him?
- Yaz!

624
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:29,827
Graham.

625
00:42:29,829 --> 00:42:32,347
Oh, what are those things?

626
00:42:32,349 --> 00:42:34,627
The creatures that live inside Daleks.

627
00:42:34,629 --> 00:42:36,427
But who built all this?!

628
00:42:36,429 --> 00:42:38,029
I have.

629
00:42:40,909 --> 00:42:43,587
- Leo?
- Don't get too close!

630
00:42:43,589 --> 00:42:45,307
I warned you about that thing.

631
00:42:45,309 --> 00:42:47,067
What have you done, Leo?

632
00:42:47,069 --> 00:42:50,827
Cloned the smallest
trace of organic material,

633
00:42:50,829 --> 00:42:53,638
not understanding that
Dalek consciousness

634
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:56,306
can live within the tiniest
fragment of their DNA.

635
00:42:56,308 --> 00:42:57,717
You weren't to know.

636
00:42:57,719 --> 00:42:59,278
You're safe. We're here for you.

637
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:00,958
We're going to get
you out of here alive.

638
00:43:00,960 --> 00:43:02,987
You give this body false hope.

639
00:43:02,989 --> 00:43:06,707
All right, then, Dalek,
or whatever you are,

640
00:43:06,709 --> 00:43:08,867
tell me how you've built all this.

641
00:43:08,869 --> 00:43:12,387
I connected myself
into the neural network.

642
00:43:12,389 --> 00:43:17,307
I inserted myself into the
organisation, into every network.

643
00:43:17,309 --> 00:43:20,109
I located this place, created it.

644
00:43:21,090 --> 00:43:25,090
Every piece of equipment,
every idea behind it...

645
00:43:26,909 --> 00:43:28,587
...I did that.

646
00:43:28,589 --> 00:43:30,667
Wait a minute. First of
all, that's not possible.

647
00:43:30,669 --> 00:43:33,267
Where did you get the purchase
order numbers in the first place?

648
00:43:33,269 --> 00:43:35,547
Really, that's what's
bugging you most right now?

649
00:43:35,549 --> 00:43:38,439
I used your systems
to buy this building,

650
00:43:38,441 --> 00:43:39,838
to order equipment,

651
00:43:39,840 --> 00:43:44,147
to pay humans to construct
and to continue the clone work.

652
00:43:44,149 --> 00:43:49,918
I used your systems to build
an army all in my image.

653
00:43:49,920 --> 00:43:51,799
But where are the workers?

654
00:43:51,801 --> 00:43:53,947
Where are the people
who did all the cloning?

655
00:43:53,949 --> 00:43:57,629
Once the experiments
were working, they became...

656
00:43:59,357 --> 00:44:00,757
...unnecessary.

657
00:44:01,769 --> 00:44:04,049
We found them another use.

658
00:44:07,549 --> 00:44:11,449
What, you're feeding cloned
Dalek creatures liquidised humans?

659
00:44:12,589 --> 00:44:13,907
Correct.

660
00:44:13,909 --> 00:44:15,707
This is a PR disaster.

661
00:44:15,709 --> 00:44:18,307
But there's something
else that's bugging me.

662
00:44:18,309 --> 00:44:20,467
- What is it?
- Is it the light?

663
00:44:20,469 --> 00:44:23,267
The light's been changing really
slowly ever since we've been here.

664
00:44:23,269 --> 00:44:25,880
Yes, it is. Thanks, Yaz.
I missed you, Yaz.

665
00:44:25,882 --> 00:44:27,158
Right, why is that important?

666
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:30,147
Oh, there's too much
going on. Where was I?

667
00:44:30,149 --> 00:44:32,228
Yes. How are you going
to get off this planet?

668
00:44:32,230 --> 00:44:34,067
We will not.

669
00:44:34,069 --> 00:44:35,187
I'm sorry?

670
00:44:35,189 --> 00:44:38,267
The planet is ours.
It will be converted.

671
00:44:38,269 --> 00:44:39,917
Converted into what?

672
00:44:39,919 --> 00:44:41,878
We shall use this planet as a base

673
00:44:41,880 --> 00:44:45,187
from which to conquer this
sector of the universe.

674
00:44:45,189 --> 00:44:47,667
There's a long way between
squatting in a Japanese lab

675
00:44:47,669 --> 00:44:48,987
and subjugating humanity.

676
00:44:48,989 --> 00:44:50,507
I mean, you don't even have bodies.

677
00:44:50,509 --> 00:44:52,947
What are you going to do?
Order people from your tanks?

678
00:44:52,949 --> 00:44:56,109
Even if you made it to those shells
down there, which you can't.

679
00:44:58,376 --> 00:44:59,535
You can't.

680
00:44:59,537 --> 00:45:01,977
I mean, you definitely can't. The...

681
00:45:03,167 --> 00:45:06,306
Those shells aren't even weaponised.
They're not proper Daleks.

682
00:45:06,308 --> 00:45:08,348
- He built them.
- Doctor...

683
00:45:09,269 --> 00:45:11,027
...what's the matter?

684
00:45:11,029 --> 00:45:12,108
The light.

685
00:45:13,189 --> 00:45:15,947
The shells were built in his factories.

686
00:45:15,949 --> 00:45:19,107
Do you think I've not
augmented those designs also?

687
00:45:19,109 --> 00:45:21,507
Where's the light? We
have to turn off the light!

688
00:45:21,509 --> 00:45:22,627
Why, Doctor?

689
00:45:22,629 --> 00:45:23,867
Ultraviolet light.

690
00:45:23,869 --> 00:45:26,387
The Recon Dalek used it
to come back together.

691
00:45:26,389 --> 00:45:27,869
Activate!

692
00:45:30,069 --> 00:45:32,389
My project shall be complete.

693
00:45:39,069 --> 00:45:42,429
The New Dalek Army shall
have but one purpose.

694
00:45:49,029 --> 00:45:50,368
Exterminate!

695
00:45:58,709 --> 00:46:00,309
Exterminate!

696
00:46:22,869 --> 00:46:25,839
It appears that there
are some teething issues

697
00:46:25,841 --> 00:46:27,427
with the... with the drones,

698
00:46:27,429 --> 00:46:30,707
so I appeal to everybody to keep calm.

699
00:46:30,709 --> 00:46:33,127
The drones are completely
under our control,

700
00:46:33,129 --> 00:46:34,667
so we're working to shut them down...

701
00:46:34,669 --> 00:46:36,747
Territorial leader identified.

702
00:46:36,749 --> 00:46:40,507
Daleks will not be shut
down. Daleks are supreme.

703
00:46:40,509 --> 00:46:42,427
This must be some sort of a joke.

704
00:46:42,429 --> 00:46:44,707
Daleks do not joke.

705
00:46:44,709 --> 00:46:47,907
- And I do not surrender.
- Exterminate!

706
00:46:47,909 --> 00:46:51,707
This territory is the
property of the Daleks.

707
00:46:51,709 --> 00:46:54,347
Daleks are in control.

708
00:46:54,349 --> 00:46:58,107
All humanity will be exterminated.

709
00:46:58,109 --> 00:47:00,915
- How many Daleks did you build?
- Look, I don't know.

710
00:47:00,917 --> 00:47:02,236
- How many?!
- Thousands!

711
00:47:02,238 --> 00:47:03,478
Stop.

712
00:47:05,899 --> 00:47:07,298
You don't have to kill him.

713
00:47:07,300 --> 00:47:08,467
Correct.

714
00:47:08,469 --> 00:47:11,709
I do not have to, and yet...

715
00:47:21,189 --> 00:47:22,509
I'm sorry.

716
00:47:26,909 --> 00:47:28,549
Oh, Leo!

717
00:47:30,066 --> 00:47:32,826
No weapons. No time to think.

718
00:47:34,229 --> 00:47:37,669
All that time in a cell
wondering who I am.

719
00:47:39,149 --> 00:47:40,907
I'm the Doctor.

720
00:47:40,909 --> 00:47:42,709
I'm the one who stops the Daleks.

721
00:47:43,749 --> 00:47:46,987
All of you, to the TARDIS now!

722
00:47:46,989 --> 00:47:49,789
Only one thing I can
think of. Nuclear option.

723
00:47:52,629 --> 00:47:56,147
Nuclear option that might backfire.

724
00:47:56,149 --> 00:47:58,038
If it's what I think you're thinking,

725
00:47:58,040 --> 00:47:59,967
you'd better stop thinking it right now.

726
00:47:59,969 --> 00:48:01,507
Way too big a risk.

727
00:48:01,509 --> 00:48:03,507
- How big a risk?
- Planet-threatening.

728
00:48:03,509 --> 00:48:05,547
Got any better ideas?
'Cause now is your moment.

729
00:48:05,549 --> 00:48:06,949
I'm all ears.

730
00:48:08,879 --> 00:48:10,438
Exactly!

731
00:48:10,440 --> 00:48:12,027
So, what is it you're going to do?

732
00:48:12,029 --> 00:48:14,589
They're built from the
original Reconnaissance Dalek.

733
00:48:15,949 --> 00:48:18,309
I'm going to give them what
they wanted in the first place.

734
00:48:22,455 --> 00:48:25,375
- What's she doing?
- Something you never want to do.

735
00:48:40,069 --> 00:48:41,787
Doc, what have you done?

736
00:48:41,789 --> 00:48:44,347
Sent a message through the
timelines into the vortex,

737
00:48:44,349 --> 00:48:47,769
'cause I know they're in
there, like sharks in water.

738
00:48:49,189 --> 00:48:51,429
Always scoping, always ready.

739
00:49:01,989 --> 00:49:05,627
Incoming reconnaissance signal detected.

740
00:49:05,629 --> 00:49:07,167
Strategise!

741
00:49:07,169 --> 00:49:09,867
Programme destination for Earth.

742
00:49:09,869 --> 00:49:12,629
Resistance must be expected!

743
00:49:13,798 --> 00:49:17,158
Ready attack formation protocols!

744
00:49:18,469 --> 00:49:19,987
Who's in there?

745
00:49:19,989 --> 00:49:22,387
The ship you never want to
see arriving on your planet.

746
00:49:22,389 --> 00:49:24,867
- What's on it?
- Death Squad Daleks.

747
00:49:24,869 --> 00:49:26,787
Think of them like the SAS of Daleks.

748
00:49:26,789 --> 00:49:29,707
- Only way more brutal.
- They're our best hope right now.

749
00:49:29,709 --> 00:49:31,307
But they're going to kill more humans.

750
00:49:31,309 --> 00:49:33,267
They don't care about humans.

751
00:49:33,269 --> 00:49:35,507
They're the enforcers of the Dalek race.

752
00:49:35,509 --> 00:49:37,867
To combat Daleks, you've
brought more Daleks?

753
00:49:37,869 --> 00:49:40,307
Yes, but they don't know that
I'm behind the transmission,

754
00:49:40,309 --> 00:49:42,907
and it's quite important that
they don't realise I'm here.

755
00:49:42,909 --> 00:49:44,987
We've got previous.
We're not best mates.

756
00:49:44,989 --> 00:49:47,278
All right, look, so if your plan works

757
00:49:47,280 --> 00:49:49,446
and this set of Daleks kills his lot...

758
00:49:49,448 --> 00:49:51,087
- It's not my lot.
- Thank you.

759
00:49:51,089 --> 00:49:52,787
...how do we get rid of the new ones?

760
00:49:52,789 --> 00:49:55,067
That's phase two of the
plan. It'll be down to us.

761
00:49:55,069 --> 00:49:57,587
Feeble humans, do not run!

762
00:49:57,589 --> 00:50:00,547
Your bodies are too slow for Daleks!

763
00:50:00,549 --> 00:50:04,067
Daleks are in control of this territory!

764
00:50:04,069 --> 00:50:07,149
Humans shall be exterminated!

765
00:50:09,613 --> 00:50:12,947
The New Dalek Army is in control!

766
00:50:12,949 --> 00:50:15,067
Daleks are reborn!

767
00:50:15,069 --> 00:50:19,667
Nothing shall stop the supremacy
of the New Dalek Army!

768
00:50:29,509 --> 00:50:31,346
Analysis!

769
00:50:31,348 --> 00:50:34,787
Scan determines rogue creatures below!

770
00:50:34,789 --> 00:50:37,747
Mutated Dalek DNA detected!

771
00:50:37,749 --> 00:50:42,589
Prepare for maximum extermination!

772
00:50:45,869 --> 00:50:48,994
Primary rogue impurities located!

773
00:50:48,996 --> 00:50:53,507
Isolate and engage primary
rogue Dalek impurities!

774
00:50:53,509 --> 00:50:57,676
Seek and destroy all
other Dalek impurities!

775
00:50:57,678 --> 00:51:01,838
Engaging primary rogue Dalek impurities!

776
00:51:01,840 --> 00:51:04,078
Halt. Stay where you are!

777
00:51:04,080 --> 00:51:06,387
- Daleks are now in control!
- In control!

778
00:51:06,389 --> 00:51:08,627
In control!

779
00:51:08,629 --> 00:51:11,317
Daleks are already in control.

780
00:51:11,319 --> 00:51:12,998
Identify!

781
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:14,267
Dalek!

782
00:51:14,269 --> 00:51:17,958
Incorrect. Scan detects anomalies.

783
00:51:17,960 --> 00:51:21,438
Dalek DNA merged with human traces.

784
00:51:21,440 --> 00:51:25,427
We have mutated to survive.

785
00:51:25,429 --> 00:51:30,667
You are impure! The Dalek
race must have purity!

786
00:51:30,669 --> 00:51:32,667
Exterminate!

787
00:51:32,669 --> 00:51:35,267
Exterminate the impurities!

788
00:51:35,269 --> 00:51:39,349
- Exterminate the impurities!
- Exterminate the impurities!

789
00:51:43,199 --> 00:51:44,918
That's the thing about Daleks.

790
00:51:44,920 --> 00:51:46,439
For a race born out of mutation,

791
00:51:46,441 --> 00:51:48,158
they're pretty obsessed with purity.

792
00:51:48,160 --> 00:51:50,147
All that product.

793
00:51:50,149 --> 00:51:52,547
Maybe I can make a claim on insurance.

794
00:51:52,549 --> 00:51:54,269
Get back in the TARDIS.

795
00:51:55,309 --> 00:51:57,569
I don't take my orders from you, Doctor.

796
00:52:00,669 --> 00:52:03,349
Those are powerful,
intelligent creatures.

797
00:52:05,309 --> 00:52:06,747
I'm backing them.

798
00:52:06,749 --> 00:52:09,349
Don't be stupid. They will kill you.

799
00:52:10,829 --> 00:52:12,547
I don't think so.

800
00:52:12,549 --> 00:52:14,107
See you later.

801
00:52:14,109 --> 00:52:16,547
Robertson, get back here!

802
00:52:25,669 --> 00:52:28,507
- Exterminate!
- Wait, wait.

803
00:52:28,509 --> 00:52:30,507
I come in peace.

804
00:52:30,509 --> 00:52:32,107
Who are you?

805
00:52:32,109 --> 00:52:34,067
I speak for humanity.

806
00:52:34,069 --> 00:52:36,873
You are the leader of this planet?

807
00:52:36,875 --> 00:52:38,227
Yes.

808
00:52:38,229 --> 00:52:40,187
And I'm your best ally here.

809
00:52:40,189 --> 00:52:43,129
Daleks do not need allies.

810
00:52:43,131 --> 00:52:45,227
I know how the Earth works.

811
00:52:45,229 --> 00:52:47,387
I have information.

812
00:52:47,389 --> 00:52:49,229
I can guide you.

813
00:52:50,429 --> 00:52:54,027
Daleks have no need of
guidance from humans.

814
00:52:54,029 --> 00:52:56,078
You are unimportant.

815
00:52:56,080 --> 00:52:58,359
I can see how you might think that,

816
00:52:58,361 --> 00:53:01,787
but, er, I'm no ordinary human.

817
00:53:01,789 --> 00:53:05,627
We shall destroy Dalek impurities!

818
00:53:05,629 --> 00:53:07,307
Of course.

819
00:53:07,309 --> 00:53:09,027
But when you're done with that,

820
00:53:09,029 --> 00:53:11,328
you're going to want
the planet too, right?

821
00:53:11,330 --> 00:53:15,730
Don't you think that would go
down well with your fellow Daleks?

822
00:53:19,819 --> 00:53:22,638
You would betray your own race?

823
00:53:22,640 --> 00:53:25,827
You would betray humanity?

824
00:53:25,829 --> 00:53:28,027
Sure.

825
00:53:28,029 --> 00:53:29,947
And I have some other information.

826
00:53:29,949 --> 00:53:31,678
The signal that brought you here...

827
00:53:31,680 --> 00:53:33,846
Explain!

828
00:53:33,848 --> 00:53:36,808
First, I want to meet
who's in charge here.

829
00:53:38,789 --> 00:53:42,427
In other words, take me to your leader.

830
00:53:42,429 --> 00:53:44,707
Phase one of the plan is working.

831
00:53:44,709 --> 00:53:47,187
Daleks destroying other Daleks

832
00:53:47,189 --> 00:53:48,667
in order to save humanity.

833
00:53:48,669 --> 00:53:50,597
Now, phase two.

834
00:53:50,599 --> 00:53:53,278
Jack, how do you feel about
boarding an SAS Dalek ship?

835
00:53:53,280 --> 00:53:55,198
- Can I blow it up?
- Yes, please.

836
00:53:55,200 --> 00:53:56,347
My kind of plan.

837
00:53:56,349 --> 00:53:58,387
- I have Dalek issues.
- No kidding?

838
00:53:58,389 --> 00:54:00,267
You never forget your first death.

839
00:54:00,269 --> 00:54:02,147
Me and Graham are coming with you.

840
00:54:02,149 --> 00:54:04,750
- Are we?
- Big Dalek ship, only one guy.

841
00:54:04,752 --> 00:54:06,992
If we don't help, the
human race is going down.

842
00:54:08,149 --> 00:54:10,267
Yeah, yeah, he's right.
We're coming with you.

843
00:54:10,269 --> 00:54:11,969
Whoa, whoa, are you okay with this?

844
00:54:15,589 --> 00:54:18,197
I couldn't stop them
even if I wanted to.

845
00:54:18,199 --> 00:54:20,078
No detonation until we're sure

846
00:54:20,080 --> 00:54:23,073
that the SAS Daleks have destroyed
all of Robertson's creations.

847
00:54:23,075 --> 00:54:26,707
And before you're all clear
of the Dalek ship, obviously.

848
00:54:26,709 --> 00:54:29,989
Obviously. We didn't come this
far just to get exterminated.

849
00:54:32,429 --> 00:54:34,467
Okay, boys. Hold tight.

850
00:54:34,469 --> 00:54:37,087
'Cause here we go.

851
00:54:38,189 --> 00:54:39,469
Right.

852
00:54:43,549 --> 00:54:46,398
Okay, command centre is down that way.

853
00:54:46,400 --> 00:54:48,918
Do not go that way. That's
where most of the Daleks will be.

854
00:54:48,920 --> 00:54:50,427
- Are you clear on what to do?
- Yeah.

855
00:54:50,429 --> 00:54:52,627
Spread these things out
and don't get killed.

856
00:54:52,629 --> 00:54:55,069
- That's it. Good luck.
- Oh...

857
00:55:00,109 --> 00:55:04,918
That's it, eh? Ryan, see,
this is our area of expertise.

858
00:55:04,920 --> 00:55:07,202
First, the Cyber dudes, now the Daleks

859
00:55:07,204 --> 00:55:09,724
no alien ship is safe
from us two bad boys.

860
00:55:13,389 --> 00:55:15,507
What?

861
00:55:15,509 --> 00:55:17,589
Stop talking weird, Graham.

862
00:55:20,789 --> 00:55:22,309
Sorry.

863
00:55:25,549 --> 00:55:28,918
Alert! Internal ship sensors report

864
00:55:28,920 --> 00:55:30,987
non-Dalek life forms on board!

865
00:55:30,989 --> 00:55:35,869
Seek, locate and exterminate
all non-Dalek life forms!

866
00:55:49,509 --> 00:55:52,107
Okay! Who's in charge here?

867
00:55:52,109 --> 00:55:54,787
I only want to talk to the boss.

868
00:55:54,789 --> 00:55:56,509
Speak!

869
00:55:58,229 --> 00:56:03,107
Well, first of all, you need
to know that I'm on your side.

870
00:56:03,109 --> 00:56:06,627
Now, to prove that, I can tell you this

871
00:56:06,629 --> 00:56:08,829
you're all headed into a trap.

872
00:56:10,789 --> 00:56:14,707
The person who summoned
you, she's called the Doctor.

873
00:56:14,709 --> 00:56:18,438
The Doctor is an enemy
of the Dalek race!

874
00:56:18,440 --> 00:56:21,267
I know. So, here's the deal.

875
00:56:21,269 --> 00:56:24,787
You let me live, I help you find her.

876
00:56:24,789 --> 00:56:26,910
You've got to be kidding me!

877
00:56:26,912 --> 00:56:30,998
Incoming emergency
spatial shift! Exterminate!

878
00:56:31,000 --> 00:56:34,707
Do not exterminate. I am Dalek. Halt!

879
00:56:34,709 --> 00:56:38,678
We have exterminated all impurities!

880
00:56:38,680 --> 00:56:42,398
You are the final remaining impurity!

881
00:56:42,400 --> 00:56:44,587
I am not impure.

882
00:56:44,589 --> 00:56:47,627
I am a survivor

883
00:56:47,629 --> 00:56:51,627
the last remains of a
reconnaissance scout.

884
00:56:51,629 --> 00:56:55,027
I surveyed this planet.

885
00:56:55,029 --> 00:56:58,187
I attempted to alert the fleet.

886
00:56:58,189 --> 00:57:03,158
I have served, given my
life for the Dalek cause.

887
00:57:03,160 --> 00:57:05,987
But you are impure.

888
00:57:05,989 --> 00:57:09,107
I can be purified.

889
00:57:09,109 --> 00:57:12,368
My genetics can be modified.

890
00:57:12,370 --> 00:57:15,827
There is only one purification.

891
00:57:15,829 --> 00:57:18,089
Exterminate!

892
00:57:23,829 --> 00:57:27,558
- Argh!
- Jack, explosives all laid. Good to go.

893
00:57:27,560 --> 00:57:29,187
- Sort of.
- What do you mean?

894
00:57:29,189 --> 00:57:31,667
Doctor, I've got some good
news and some bad news.

895
00:57:31,669 --> 00:57:33,327
The good news is

896
00:57:33,329 --> 00:57:35,787
the last of Robertson's
Daleks has been destroyed.

897
00:57:35,789 --> 00:57:37,707
Can we stop there and
pretend there's no bad news?

898
00:57:37,709 --> 00:57:40,467
The bad news is Robertson is
negotiating with the Daleks

899
00:57:40,469 --> 00:57:41,507
and has sold you out.

900
00:57:41,509 --> 00:57:45,627
The Daleks know it was you
who brought them here, as a trap.

901
00:57:45,629 --> 00:57:47,309
I knew I wouldn't like the bad news.

902
00:57:48,349 --> 00:57:49,587
What do we do?

903
00:57:49,589 --> 00:57:51,649
Right, just running
through the options...

904
00:57:52,589 --> 00:57:53,947
...which hasn't taken long.

905
00:57:53,949 --> 00:57:55,267
Even if we blow up the ship,

906
00:57:55,269 --> 00:57:58,086
there's still SAS Daleks
marauding through Earth's skies,

907
00:57:58,088 --> 00:58:00,307
and now they know I'm here!

908
00:58:00,309 --> 00:58:02,147
So we have to keep you out their way.

909
00:58:02,149 --> 00:58:04,187
Or...

910
00:58:04,189 --> 00:58:05,307
Or what?

911
00:58:05,309 --> 00:58:08,107
- Shh. Working.
- Doctor, tell me.

912
00:58:08,109 --> 00:58:10,027
You're going to have to
trust me on this, Yaz.

913
00:58:10,029 --> 00:58:12,029
When have I ever let you down before?

914
00:58:17,549 --> 00:58:19,827
I won't disappear again.

915
00:58:19,829 --> 00:58:21,889
Yeah, you will.

916
00:58:23,050 --> 00:58:24,290
One day, you will.

917
00:58:29,830 --> 00:58:31,347
Where are we?

918
00:58:31,349 --> 00:58:33,547
Right, come here and monitor this timer.

919
00:58:33,549 --> 00:58:34,919
Jack, I need you to be ready

920
00:58:34,921 --> 00:58:36,427
to get everyone off
that ship and detonate.

921
00:58:36,429 --> 00:58:37,587
Yaz will tell you when.

922
00:58:37,589 --> 00:58:39,467
What about the other Daleks?

923
00:58:39,469 --> 00:58:40,869
I'm dealing with them!

924
00:58:44,730 --> 00:58:45,787
Hey.

925
00:58:45,789 --> 00:58:47,147
I'm a bit lost.

926
00:58:48,470 --> 00:58:49,787
Alert, alert!

927
00:58:49,789 --> 00:58:51,867
Didn't sound good. Do
you want to get that?

928
00:58:51,869 --> 00:58:53,667
Remain here.

929
00:58:53,669 --> 00:58:57,198
All Dalek units, report
to central control.

930
00:58:57,200 --> 00:58:59,387
The Doctor is detected!

931
00:58:59,389 --> 00:59:02,436
Extermination formations, assemble!

932
00:59:02,438 --> 00:59:04,238
TARDIS location identified!

933
00:59:04,240 --> 00:59:07,227
Give us one good reason why
we should save your life.

934
00:59:07,229 --> 00:59:08,467
Money?

935
00:59:08,469 --> 00:59:10,827
- I still say we should leave him here.
- Yeah.

936
00:59:10,829 --> 00:59:12,307
Exterminate!

937
00:59:12,309 --> 00:59:13,747
Go!

938
00:59:13,749 --> 00:59:17,749
The Doctor's TARDIS is located.
Surround the TARDIS!

939
00:59:19,629 --> 00:59:21,627
Hey! Daleks!

940
00:59:21,629 --> 00:59:24,587
- Over here!
- It is the Doctor!

941
00:59:24,589 --> 00:59:27,318
The Doctor is an enemy of the Daleks!

942
00:59:27,320 --> 00:59:29,347
Yes, it is. And, yes, I am.

943
00:59:29,349 --> 00:59:33,517
I called you here and you
came, like obedient little pets.

944
00:59:33,519 --> 00:59:35,038
Thanks for solving my problem.

945
00:59:35,040 --> 00:59:37,627
Daleks are not pets of the Doctor!

946
00:59:37,629 --> 00:59:39,846
Yes, you are. Why? What are
you going to do about it?

947
00:59:39,848 --> 00:59:41,887
'Cause I'm just standing
here, in my TARDIS.

948
00:59:41,889 --> 00:59:45,089
Attack the TARDIS!
Exterminate the Doctor!

949
00:59:48,429 --> 00:59:50,307
You're sure this is the right way?

950
00:59:50,309 --> 00:59:52,588
- There's Daleks everywhere!
- We've got to get us out of here.

951
00:59:52,590 --> 00:59:54,027
You are intruders!

952
00:59:54,029 --> 00:59:55,678
This is a terrible rescue!

953
00:59:55,680 --> 00:59:58,278
Intruders located!
Life forms identified!

954
00:59:58,280 --> 00:59:59,667
We're surrounded!

955
00:59:59,669 --> 01:00:01,998
- Do not move!
- Do not move!

956
01:00:02,000 --> 01:00:04,027
Hey, are we ready? Do I detonate?

957
01:00:04,029 --> 01:00:06,067
Almost. Grab hold.

958
01:00:06,069 --> 01:00:08,118
Now, Jack! Get off the ship!

959
01:00:08,120 --> 01:00:10,747
Intruders, identify!

960
01:00:10,749 --> 01:00:14,827
I'm Captain Jack Harkness.
And I'm immortal. Ha!

961
01:00:14,829 --> 01:00:16,909
Exterminate!

962
01:00:23,349 --> 01:00:26,307
Dalek craft destroyed!

963
01:00:26,309 --> 01:00:28,067
Where is the Doctor?!

964
01:00:28,069 --> 01:00:31,398
Search the TARDIS!
Exterminate the Doctor!

965
01:00:31,400 --> 01:00:35,438
Oh, mate! You fell
for the old switcheroo.

966
01:00:35,440 --> 01:00:38,067
Awkward. That's not my TARDIS.

967
01:00:38,069 --> 01:00:39,998
I had a spare one lying around,

968
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:42,327
so I used the chameleon circuit
to make it look like mine,

969
01:00:42,329 --> 01:00:43,557
and guess who fell for it?

970
01:00:43,559 --> 01:00:44,678
You guys.

971
01:00:44,680 --> 01:00:46,507
We shall find you!

972
01:00:46,509 --> 01:00:49,187
We have control of a TARDIS!

973
01:00:49,189 --> 01:00:52,728
No. You don't. Sorry.

974
01:00:52,730 --> 01:00:56,438
More bad news. I've programmed
it to fold in on itself

975
01:00:56,440 --> 01:00:59,107
and send itself to
the heart of the Void,

976
01:00:59,109 --> 01:01:01,107
which will of course break it apart

977
01:01:01,109 --> 01:01:03,547
and destroy you in the process.

978
01:01:03,549 --> 01:01:04,987
Thanks for helping today.

979
01:01:04,989 --> 01:01:06,507
Won't be seeing you later.

980
01:01:06,509 --> 01:01:09,358
You will not escape us, Doctor!

981
01:01:09,360 --> 01:01:11,809
Yes, I will. Every time.

982
01:01:24,941 --> 01:01:27,798
- Oh, that was horrible.
- I feel sick.

983
01:01:27,800 --> 01:01:29,158
What just happened to me?

984
01:01:29,160 --> 01:01:30,187
Did we do it?

985
01:01:30,189 --> 01:01:32,030
We did it!

986
01:01:32,032 --> 01:01:34,267
Daleks all exiled.

987
01:01:34,269 --> 01:01:36,489
Now, you have got a
lot of explaining to do.

988
01:01:39,149 --> 01:01:41,869
I was deliberately acting as a decoy.

989
01:01:45,238 --> 01:01:47,561
They're calling him
the saviour of humanity,

990
01:01:47,563 --> 01:01:50,867
the man who stood up to the
invaders on behalf of us all.

991
01:01:50,869 --> 01:01:52,926
Now, as rumours intensify

992
01:01:52,928 --> 01:01:55,518
that he may be in line
for an honorary knighthood,

993
01:01:55,520 --> 01:01:59,507
Jack Robertson spoke to me from
his home in the United States.

994
01:01:59,509 --> 01:02:02,867
Emily, I did what any man

995
01:02:02,869 --> 01:02:06,067
person, human person

996
01:02:06,069 --> 01:02:09,187
would do in those circumstances.

997
01:02:09,189 --> 01:02:12,667
There's even talk of a revived
presidential run for you.

998
01:02:12,669 --> 01:02:16,747
Well, I can't really answer to that.

999
01:02:18,149 --> 01:02:21,089
- Can you believe that?
- Yeah, I can.

1000
01:02:23,314 --> 01:02:25,114
We should go and meet the Doc.

1001
01:02:34,949 --> 01:02:36,309
Yeah.

1002
01:02:39,669 --> 01:02:41,627
Sorry, lost track of time.

1003
01:02:41,629 --> 01:02:43,207
Gwen Cooper sends her love, by the way.

1004
01:02:43,209 --> 01:02:44,359
Says she took out a Dalek

1005
01:02:44,361 --> 01:02:46,398
with a moped and her
son's boxing gloves.

1006
01:02:46,400 --> 01:02:47,879
Hoo-hoo! Anyway,

1007
01:02:47,881 --> 01:02:50,227
I'm going to stick around on
Earth and catch up with her.

1008
01:02:50,229 --> 01:02:51,267
I'll call ya.

1009
01:02:51,269 --> 01:02:54,427
Send my love to Gwen. Okay, bye!

1010
01:02:54,429 --> 01:02:55,787
Right, fam,

1011
01:02:55,789 --> 01:02:59,076
I thought we could try
the Meringue Galaxy.

1012
01:02:59,078 --> 01:03:01,598
It's not a place, it's a restaurant

1013
01:03:01,600 --> 01:03:03,747
where every course is meringue.

1014
01:03:03,749 --> 01:03:05,707
And the furniture.

1015
01:03:05,709 --> 01:03:09,107
- Plus the waiters!
- Love it!

1016
01:03:09,109 --> 01:03:10,839
- All set?
- Ready.

1017
01:03:10,841 --> 01:03:11,861
Yep.

1018
01:03:15,149 --> 01:03:16,589
Nah.

1019
01:03:20,469 --> 01:03:22,389
I think I'm going to stay here.

1020
01:03:28,069 --> 01:03:29,787
Yeah.

1021
01:03:29,789 --> 01:03:31,307
Yeah.

1022
01:03:31,309 --> 01:03:33,229
Me mates need me.

1023
01:03:34,789 --> 01:03:37,072
And I know this sounds stupid, but...

1024
01:03:37,074 --> 01:03:38,994
...I feel like my planet needs me.

1025
01:03:41,029 --> 01:03:42,789
You've got to fight for it, right?

1026
01:03:44,469 --> 01:03:45,867
Look, Doctor, before...

1027
01:03:45,869 --> 01:03:48,987
...before I met you, I didn't know
what I wanted to do with me life.

1028
01:03:48,989 --> 01:03:50,389
And...

1029
01:03:51,749 --> 01:03:53,109
And now... And now, I know.

1030
01:04:00,109 --> 01:04:01,669
Ten months.

1031
01:04:03,669 --> 01:04:05,349
I made it back too late.

1032
01:04:06,589 --> 01:04:08,229
Missed my time with you.

1033
01:04:10,229 --> 01:04:12,109
So, are we hugging, or...?

1034
01:04:24,752 --> 01:04:27,751
What about you two?
Are you going to...?

1035
01:04:27,753 --> 01:04:29,473
Stay? Yeah, definitely.

1036
01:04:30,509 --> 01:04:32,069
Yes!

1037
01:04:33,429 --> 01:04:36,107
I'm not ready to let you go yet.

1038
01:04:36,109 --> 01:04:37,909
That's all right, isn't it?

1039
01:04:38,952 --> 01:04:40,672
You've said it now, so...

1040
01:04:42,909 --> 01:04:45,349
Of course it's all right. She needs you.

1041
01:04:47,069 --> 01:04:48,827
- Yes for Yaz!
- Hey.

1042
01:04:48,829 --> 01:04:51,067
You're getting over me
leaving quick enough.

1043
01:04:51,069 --> 01:04:52,429
Two hearts.

1044
01:04:53,909 --> 01:04:55,309
One happy...

1045
01:04:56,713 --> 01:04:58,313
...one sad.

1046
01:05:00,109 --> 01:05:02,307
Make sure she doesn't
get in any trouble.

1047
01:05:02,309 --> 01:05:04,787
It's going to be difficult.

1048
01:05:04,789 --> 01:05:07,491
I'm holding you responsible
for the planet while I'm away.

1049
01:05:07,493 --> 01:05:08,693
Yeah. Deal.

1050
01:05:09,789 --> 01:05:10,869
Graham?

1051
01:05:14,029 --> 01:05:15,907
Look, it's all right, you know.

1052
01:05:15,909 --> 01:05:20,267
I'm all grown up now,
so... you can go with them.

1053
01:05:20,269 --> 01:05:22,029
Yeah, well...

1054
01:05:24,598 --> 01:05:27,317
Yeah, well, you know,
there's lots to explore,

1055
01:05:27,319 --> 01:05:29,507
so much more to see.

1056
01:05:29,509 --> 01:05:30,549
You know...

1057
01:05:32,309 --> 01:05:33,349
But, um...

1058
01:05:35,913 --> 01:05:37,912
I don't want to miss out on you,

1059
01:05:37,914 --> 01:05:41,707
you know, and being here
without you ain't going to be...

1060
01:05:41,709 --> 01:05:43,069
...the same.

1061
01:05:44,349 --> 01:05:47,027
You know, I'll always
be looking around, then,

1062
01:05:47,029 --> 01:05:49,109
to say stuff to you, you know?

1063
01:05:50,669 --> 01:05:52,269
You see, Ryan, you're my family.

1064
01:05:54,269 --> 01:05:56,347
And I remember, Doc,
what you said, you know,

1065
01:05:56,349 --> 01:05:59,707
that we... we wouldn't come back
the same people, and you're right.

1066
01:05:59,709 --> 01:06:03,149
Just not in the way I thought.

1067
01:06:05,749 --> 01:06:07,987
I'm ready. I want to...

1068
01:06:07,989 --> 01:06:10,189
I want to be at home with my grandson.

1069
01:06:14,050 --> 01:06:15,267
What?

1070
01:06:15,269 --> 01:06:17,867
I just thought I'd have the
place to myself, you know.

1071
01:06:17,869 --> 01:06:19,989
No such luck.

1072
01:06:22,109 --> 01:06:24,189
Yaz.

1073
01:06:27,389 --> 01:06:28,869
I'm sure I'll see you soon, eh?

1074
01:06:30,629 --> 01:06:32,347
Keep doing humanity proud.

1075
01:06:32,349 --> 01:06:34,349
I'm going to miss you.

1076
01:06:37,189 --> 01:06:38,669
Doc.

1077
01:06:39,829 --> 01:06:42,507
Thank you so much.

1078
01:06:42,509 --> 01:06:44,667
Right...

1079
01:06:44,669 --> 01:06:47,187
Well, come on, son.

1080
01:06:47,189 --> 01:06:49,029
Hey...

1081
01:06:54,909 --> 01:06:56,589
Bye, fam.

1082
01:06:59,469 --> 01:07:01,149
Yeah.

1083
01:07:05,229 --> 01:07:06,788
Right...

1084
01:07:09,429 --> 01:07:11,148
Wait.

1085
01:07:16,989 --> 01:07:19,067
Take these. Might come in handy.

1086
01:07:19,069 --> 01:07:21,749
Oh. Ta.

1087
01:07:25,349 --> 01:07:27,387
Oh!

1088
01:07:27,389 --> 01:07:30,309
And, Doc, I was wrong.

1089
01:07:31,869 --> 01:07:33,589
We do get aliens in Sheffield.

1090
01:07:42,349 --> 01:07:44,199
I could always use
the TARDIS to go back,

1091
01:07:44,201 --> 01:07:46,427
arrive an hour after you guys,

1092
01:07:46,429 --> 01:07:47,889
change the timeline.

1093
01:07:49,789 --> 01:07:51,789
Then we'd have more time together.

1094
01:07:53,429 --> 01:07:55,229
It's okay to be sad.

1095
01:08:05,509 --> 01:08:08,467
Okay, three, two,

1096
01:08:08,469 --> 01:08:10,907
one, go!

1097
01:08:10,909 --> 01:08:13,147
Yes, go on, Ryan!

1098
01:08:13,149 --> 01:08:14,627
You're doing it, son!

1099
01:08:14,629 --> 01:08:16,414
Go on, son!

1100
01:08:16,416 --> 01:08:18,336
Come on!

1101
01:08:21,750 --> 01:08:23,029
All right.

1102
01:08:24,069 --> 01:08:26,627
Ryan, you okay, son?

1103
01:08:26,629 --> 01:08:28,329
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah?

1104
01:08:29,429 --> 01:08:31,187
Well, look, definitely further.

1105
01:08:31,189 --> 01:08:34,067
- Yeah. Maybe.
- No, definitely.

1106
01:08:34,069 --> 01:08:36,029
I was looking online earlier...

1107
01:08:37,789 --> 01:08:40,547
Some weird stuff going on
in a village in Finland.

1108
01:08:40,549 --> 01:08:43,067
Troll invasion, so
the locals are saying.

1109
01:08:43,069 --> 01:08:44,907
Yeah, I saw that.

1110
01:08:44,909 --> 01:08:48,387
And, you know, there's a quarry
in Korea that's shut down

1111
01:08:48,389 --> 01:08:49,768
because the workers are reporting

1112
01:08:49,770 --> 01:08:51,450
they saw gravel creatures come to life.

1113
01:08:59,309 --> 01:09:00,667
Psychic paper.

1114
01:09:00,669 --> 01:09:03,118
Yeah. These will get us in anywhere.

1115
01:09:03,120 --> 01:09:04,698
Yeah, Finland, Korea...

1116
01:09:04,700 --> 01:09:07,423
- Well, then, what are we waiting for?
- I'm not done here yet.

1117
01:09:07,425 --> 01:09:09,507
Yeah, but, look... I mean, this...

1118
01:09:09,509 --> 01:09:11,307
You'll be black and blue.

1119
01:09:11,309 --> 01:09:14,547
I don't know if you heard
about me, but I'm Ryan Sinclair.

1120
01:09:14,549 --> 01:09:17,598
Me and me mates, we saw off everything

1121
01:09:17,600 --> 01:09:20,467
from giant spiders to
a conscious universe.

1122
01:09:20,469 --> 01:09:23,147
We fought Cybermen,

1123
01:09:23,149 --> 01:09:25,747
Skithra, Morax...

1124
01:09:25,749 --> 01:09:27,029
...the mighty Pting.

1125
01:09:28,509 --> 01:09:31,307
It's going to take more
than a bike to scare me off.

1126
01:09:31,309 --> 01:09:34,587
Ain't that right, Grandad?

1127
01:09:34,589 --> 01:09:36,107
Yeah.

1128
01:09:36,109 --> 01:09:38,829
Right, then. Well, come
on, then. Jump on, then.

1129
01:09:44,549 --> 01:09:47,229
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1130
01:10:08,349 --> 01:10:10,867
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1131
01:10:10,869 --> 01:10:14,187
Yeah, uh, just got the sun in me eyes.

1132
01:10:14,189 --> 01:10:15,549
Yeah, me too.

1133
01:10:16,989 --> 01:10:19,947
Right, a few more tries and
we'll go and save the world, eh?

1134
01:10:19,949 --> 01:10:21,667
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1135
01:10:21,669 --> 01:10:23,481
Here we go, get ready.

1136
01:10:23,483 --> 01:10:25,907
Three, two, one...

1137
01:10:25,909 --> 01:10:28,027
Go! Go on, Ryan.

1138
01:10:28,029 --> 01:10:30,547
Yeah! Go on, son!

1139
01:10:30,549 --> 01:10:32,069
You're doing it, mate!

